faculty to disseminate

00:39:29.540 --> 00:39:32.705
this kind of information
is also important.

00:39:32.705 --> 00:39:37.010
And another thing is creating
some school-based databases

00:39:37.010 --> 00:39:39.330
of all the available
resources within the school,

00:39:39.330 --> 00:39:43.080
whether that be different room
locations, or technologies,

00:39:43.080 --> 00:39:45.775
or even people, so that it's
easy for separate faculty

00:39:45.775 --> 00:39:49.110
to just access that and know
who to contact and who to reach.

00:39:49.110 --> 00:39:52.000
And I think having those teams,
as that group had brought up,

00:39:52.000 --> 00:39:54.810
with instruction designers and
all that dedicated towards you

00:39:54.810 --> 00:39:55.655
is a great resource.

00:39:59.680 --> 00:40:01.850
How about this group?

00:40:01.850 --> 00:40:02.710
Thank you.

00:40:02.710 --> 00:40:05.890
So I think we started off
by just kind of comparing

00:40:05.890 --> 00:40:10.630
and sharing how our different
institutions approach

00:40:10.630 --> 00:40:14.020
supporting faculty and
teaching assistants and really

00:40:14.020 --> 00:40:15.190
folks at all levels.

00:40:15.190 --> 00:40:16.960
And I think much of
what's been said here

00:40:16.960 --> 00:40:17.959
is what we've discussed.

00:40:17.959 --> 00:40:20.500
But really thinking about
support in a very systematic

00:40:20.500 --> 00:40:24.850
way, starting with onboarding,
with mentoring, with the peer

00:40:24.850 --> 00:40:27.310
observation, with evaluation.

00:40:27.310 --> 00:40:30.940
I think for me a big piece
of that is also the culture--

00:40:30.940 --> 00:40:34.810
the culture and the emphasis
on the importance of teaching,

00:40:34.810 --> 00:40:37.090
and how do we make
it more visible?

00:40:37.090 --> 00:40:39.962
So I think really a lot
of what everybody has said

00:40:39.962 --> 00:40:40.920
has been captured here.

00:40:40.920 --> 00:40:44.740
And then the alignment of that
with the incentives and really

00:40:44.740 --> 00:40:46.930
making sure that they are
aligned, that there aren't

00:40:46.930 --> 00:40:49.600
perverse incentives
kind of throwing off

00:40:49.600 --> 00:40:53.040
the purpose of making teaching
a focus of the institution

00:40:53.040 --> 00:40:53.540
as well.

00:40:58.360 --> 00:41:00.490
And I think we have
one more table.

00:41:00.490 --> 00:41:02.240
I saved you for last.

00:41:02.240 --> 00:41:04.460
Thank you.

00:41:04.460 --> 00:41:04.960
OK.

00:41:04.960 --> 00:41:07.360
So we may prove to
be the rebel table.

00:41:07.360 --> 00:41:11.470
But I'm going to
start with item five

00:41:11.470 --> 00:41:13.930
because what we talked
about is that the assumption

00:41:13.930 --> 00:41:15.580
that there's a need
to improve teaching

00:41:15.580 --> 00:41:17.200
may be problematic for some.

00:41:17.200 --> 00:41:18.970
Some may not see it.

00:41:18.970 --> 00:41:22.990
And so in some ways mobilizing
at the grassroots level,

00:41:22.990 --> 00:41:29.032
just start to engage everyone
in even why that may be a goal.

00:41:29.032 --> 00:41:31.240
Otherwise, we're walking in
with a lot of assumptions

00:41:31.240 --> 00:41:33.520
that create problems.

00:41:33.520 --> 00:41:34.600
And it's troublesome.

00:41:34.600 --> 00:41:36.230
It's difficult.

00:41:36.230 --> 00:41:39.840
When we looked at number one,
what's useful for faculty

00:41:39.840 --> 00:41:41.340
to improve teaching
practices, there

00:41:41.340 --> 00:41:43.510
was a very good
suggestion in terms

00:41:43.510 --> 00:41:49.120
of leadership being engaged in
real time effort and interest--

00:41:49.120 --> 00:41:53.350
maybe coming to classes, being
visible in the many teaching

00:41:53.350 --> 00:41:56.950
fora that exist in
some ways to start

00:41:56.950 --> 00:42:00.280
to shake it up a little
bit and help everyone

00:42:00.280 --> 00:42:03.040
shift their attention.

00:42:03.040 --> 00:42:06.160
In terms of challenges,
obstacles, among many,

00:42:06.160 --> 00:42:09.700
we came to the broader piece
of making the case for change--

00:42:09.700 --> 00:42:11.800
engaging stakeholders.

00:42:11.800 --> 00:42:14.500
Certainly incentives comes
up right away, but also

00:42:14.500 --> 00:42:16.716
thinking about the many
metrics that we lean on

00:42:16.716 --> 00:42:17.590
and their weaknesses.

00:42:17.590 --> 00:42:20.560
I know it was mentioned
in terms of ratings,

00:42:20.560 --> 00:42:25.720
and you had scores and things in
terms of for classes or courses

00:42:25.720 --> 00:42:28.270
that we know are weak
metrics, yet somehow they

00:42:28.270 --> 00:42:29.950
still live with us.

00:42:29.950 --> 00:42:31.810
And so how we address
that, I think,

00:42:31.810 --> 00:42:35.470
is a big issue that came
up for us many times.

00:42:35.470 --> 00:42:37.480
Item three, promising practices.

00:42:37.480 --> 00:42:39.610
We each came up with
examples and ideas

00:42:39.610 --> 00:42:42.320
in terms of engaging
faculty and developing

00:42:42.320 --> 00:42:45.820
the solutions, the programs, the
practices that then are going

00:42:45.820 --> 00:42:47.980
to affect them as end users
so that, again, they're

00:42:47.980 --> 00:42:50.420
part of the process.

00:42:50.420 --> 00:42:53.310
And then number four,
in terms of supporting

00:42:53.310 --> 00:42:56.200
at the department versus
school versus university level,

00:42:56.200 --> 00:42:58.150
certainly it can
happen on many levels,

00:42:58.150 --> 00:43:01.100
but the feeling of this
group was generally

00:43:01.100 --> 00:43:02.800
that the department
level is part

00:43:02.800 --> 00:43:05.920
of the core of where it needs
to start because there are so

00:43:05.920 --> 00:43:06.730
many differences.

00:43:06.730 --> 00:43:09.130
And it's not to have them
live in separate silos,

00:43:09.130 --> 00:43:11.512
but then deciding how
they link may be yet

00:43:11.512 --> 00:43:13.720
another piece of the process
we've just yet to learn.

00:43:13.720 --> 00:43:14.635
Did I leave anything out there?

00:43:14.635 --> 00:43:15.170
Nope.

00:43:15.170 --> 00:43:15.670
OK.

00:43:15.670 --> 00:43:16.236
Thank you.

00:43:19.980 --> 00:43:22.688
Thank you, everyone.

00:43:22.688 --> 00:43:24.330
Final to Rich.

00:43:24.330 --> 00:43:25.870
Did you have anything to add?

00:43:25.870 --> 00:43:30.660
So I had a couple of question.

00:43:30.660 --> 00:43:35.190
How many people here
are on ladder track?

00:43:35.190 --> 00:43:36.110
Oh, wow.

00:43:36.110 --> 00:43:36.865
Interesting.

00:43:36.865 --> 00:43:37.615
So relatively few.

00:43:37.615 --> 00:43:38.115
OK.

00:43:43.010 --> 00:43:45.550
And I guess we've talked
about the metrics.

00:43:45.550 --> 00:43:47.870
That was obviously
one of the themes

00:43:47.870 --> 00:43:52.040
that I heard listening in
in some of the report out.

00:43:52.040 --> 00:43:54.440
At one level,
attendance, I think,

00:43:54.440 --> 00:43:58.670
is a universal problem
in a lot of courses.

00:43:58.670 --> 00:43:59.930
Faculty get upset.

00:43:59.930 --> 00:44:01.500
People aren't coming.

00:44:01.500 --> 00:44:03.390
There's something wrong
with the students.

00:44:03.390 --> 00:44:05.390
But in terms of demonstrating
there's a problem,

00:44:05.390 --> 00:44:10.310
I'd say, if they felt there was
value added they would show up.

00:44:10.310 --> 00:44:12.860
I'm a big value added
person, that people

00:44:12.860 --> 00:44:14.570
make decisions on whether--

00:44:14.570 --> 00:44:16.970
between this and this
I can do two things.

00:44:16.970 --> 00:44:20.140
Which one's adding value
to what my goals are?

00:44:20.140 --> 00:44:22.820
If it's not adding
value they don't show up

00:44:22.820 --> 00:44:25.200
unless it's mandatory and
there's a penalty for it.

00:44:25.200 --> 00:44:28.010
So that, to me, is almost our
biggest metric that there's

00:44:28.010 --> 00:44:30.410
a problem at some level.

00:44:30.410 --> 00:44:34.840
And then I guess the
other question I have--

00:44:34.840 --> 00:44:35.690
two other things.

00:44:35.690 --> 00:44:38.840
One is the culture is
huge, and everybody

00:44:38.840 --> 00:44:40.380
talked about the culture.

00:44:40.380 --> 00:44:43.160
And all I would argue is,
don't be afraid to start.

00:44:43.160 --> 00:44:45.790
I put that slide up
seven years ago when

00:44:45.790 --> 00:44:48.020
we had a major symposium
at the med school

00:44:48.020 --> 00:44:50.122
to start talking about
peer observation.

00:44:50.122 --> 00:44:51.830
Seven years later,
we're implementing it.

00:44:51.830 --> 00:44:54.850
We've got 40 faculty
in the preclerkship.

00:44:54.850 --> 00:44:55.790
It takes time.

00:44:55.790 --> 00:44:58.660
But if we had more
people with tenure

00:44:58.660 --> 00:45:00.380
it'd probably be
easier to say that.

00:45:00.380 --> 00:45:04.449
But anyway, it takes time to get
some of these changes in place.

00:45:04.449 --> 00:45:06.740
And the one thing that we
play with a little bit in med

00:45:06.740 --> 00:45:09.770
school, and some medical schools
across the country have it--

00:45:09.770 --> 00:45:13.070
I don't know when it ever
would fly in university level--

00:45:13.070 --> 00:45:16.280
is a Department of Education.

00:45:16.280 --> 00:45:18.980
So you have your basic
department that you're in,

00:45:18.980 --> 00:45:21.530
content sort of department.

00:45:21.530 --> 00:45:23.540
But then for people
who are really

00:45:23.540 --> 00:45:25.280
making a career as
educators, there's

00:45:25.280 --> 00:45:28.220
a dual appointment in a
Department of Education

00:45:28.220 --> 00:45:30.830
within the university setting.

00:45:30.830 --> 00:45:33.440
And so it's another way
of recognizing people,

00:45:33.440 --> 00:45:35.035
incentivizing them.

00:45:35.035 --> 00:45:37.020
And there may be
some ways of getting

00:45:37.020 --> 00:45:40.070
promotions and other things
through the Department

00:45:40.070 --> 00:45:40.760
of Education.

00:45:40.760 --> 00:45:43.220
But I just saw that as
a big picture solution

00:45:43.220 --> 00:45:46.780
that, of course, would be
many years in the making.

00:45:46.780 --> 00:45:49.890
But there are some models
for that sort of notion.

00:45:49.890 --> 00:45:51.531
You already have a score.

00:45:51.531 --> 00:45:52.030
Yeah.

00:45:52.030 --> 00:45:53.150
I know.

00:45:53.150 --> 00:45:55.400
We're just different than
a Department of Education.

00:45:55.400 --> 00:45:56.280
All right.

00:45:56.280 --> 00:45:57.100
It's different.

00:45:57.100 --> 00:45:58.010
Little bit different.

00:45:58.010 --> 00:45:59.843
I wanted to add something
about the culture.

00:45:59.843 --> 00:46:02.180
I mean, actually, the next
phase of the study among some

00:46:02.180 --> 00:46:05.180
of the subgroups or
universities is really

00:46:05.180 --> 00:46:09.950
to try to do a longitudinal
survey study about really

00:46:09.950 --> 00:46:12.350
evaluating what the
culture is for teaching

00:46:12.350 --> 00:46:15.170
at a particular
institution, and then

00:46:15.170 --> 00:46:20.720
cross-correlating that with
what the emerging trend is.

00:46:20.720 --> 00:46:23.810
And so actually, if
anybody's interested in any

00:46:23.810 --> 00:46:29.990
of this next phases, do
get in contact with me.

00:46:29.990 --> 00:46:35.200
Thank you Julia, Rich, Barbara.

00:46:35.200 --> 00:46:39.865
If you could just go ahead and
make yourself take one minute

00:46:39.865 --> 00:46:43.800
and write on a card one thing--
it doesn't have to be based

00:46:43.800 --> 00:46:46.360
just on this session
but from today--

00:46:46.360 --> 00:46:48.550
that you would like to do
to change your practice.

00:46:48.550 --> 00:46:52.090
Could be a long term
thing, could be right now,

00:46:52.090 --> 00:46:53.590
could be from any point of view.

00:46:53.590 --> 00:46:55.540
But one thing that
you think you would

00:46:55.540 --> 00:47:00.500
like to do to improve teaching
and learning practice.

00:47:00.500 --> 00:47:05.140
And I say this, like, we're
all ready to go have lunch.

00:47:05.140 --> 00:47:08.980
But consolidating and forcing
yourself to commit to something

00:47:08.980 --> 00:47:10.930
that you think you
might want to do

00:47:10.930 --> 00:47:13.450
will actually make it
more likely that people

00:47:13.450 --> 00:47:16.840
will go out and do things
and improve things.

00:47:16.840 --> 00:47:22.630
And one final observation.

00:47:22.630 --> 00:47:27.560
Peter, who's sitting here, we
had a conversation last week.

00:47:27.560 --> 00:47:29.950
A faculty member deeply
involved with the School

00:47:29.950 --> 00:47:33.690
of Public Health and a number
of educational initiatives.

00:47:33.690 --> 00:47:36.000
But he's leaving
Harvard to go be

00:47:36.000 --> 00:47:38.570
a dean at another institution.

00:47:38.570 --> 00:47:41.490
So here he is, taking careful
notes, because now he's

00:47:41.490 --> 00:47:42.490
going to be a dean.

00:47:42.490 --> 00:47:46.370
He's got the responsibility
to think about.

00:47:46.370 --> 00:47:49.330
So you just you never know
where these ideas that

00:47:49.330 --> 00:47:51.550
might get reported
out could actually

00:47:51.550 --> 00:47:56.020
go-- how many students could
be affected on the west coast

00:47:56.020 --> 00:47:58.161
instead of on the east coast.

00:47:58.161 --> 00:48:00.550
So one minute to just
write something down.

00:48:00.550 --> 00:48:02.460
Thank you all.

